│ THOUGHT: The remaining crash is due to replacing the i1 icmp with an i8 value: I changed the init flag to i8 for atomic validity, but then used that i8 directly in the null-comparison  │
│ path, causing ICI->replaceAllUsesWith(LV) to mismatch types. The fix is to convert the loaded i8 InitBool to an i1 predicate (compare against zero) before replacing the icmp, and keep  │
│ constants as i1 true/false in the switch. I will insert an ICmpInst that tests the loaded i8 != 0 to produce an i1, and change the constant cases back to getTrue/getFalse. This         │
│ preserves atomic i8 for the init flag while maintaining i1 comparisons.                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/InitBool->getValueType()/Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext())/' llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp && sed -i                                                                   │
│ 's/cast<LoadInst>(LV)->setDebugLoc(LI->getDebugLoc());/cast<LoadInst>(LV)->setDebugLoc(LI->getDebugLoc());\n      LV = new ICmpInst(ICI, ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, LV,                          │
│ ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext()), 0), "initpred");/' llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp && sed -i 's/LV = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext()),       │
│ 0);/LV = ConstantInt::getFalse(GV->getContext());/' llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp && sed -i 's/LV = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext()), 1);/LV =                 │
