│ THOUGHT: The remaining crash happens because the optimization replaces an i1 icmp with an i8 value from the init flag, causing a type mismatch when replacing uses of the icmp. To fix   │
│ this while keeping atomic operations byte-sized, we should:                                                                                                                              │
│ - Keep InitBool as i8 for atomic validity.                                                                                                                                               │
│ - When loading InitBool for predicate replacement, convert the i8 to an i1 by comparing it against zero (i8 != 0) to create an i1 value suitable to replace the original icmp.           │
│ - Restore the constant cases in the predicate switch to use i1 true/false rather than i8 constants.                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will update GlobalOpt.cpp accordingly: ensure the load uses i8 type where needed, insert an icmp to produce an i1 predicate from the loaded i8, and change the constants in the switch │
│ back to getTrue/getFalse.                                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i 's/Value *LV = new LoadInst(InitBool->getValueType(), InitBool,/Value *LV = new LoadInst(Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext()), InitBool,/' llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp &&  │
│ sed -i 's/cast<LoadInst>(LV)->setDebugLoc(LI->getDebugLoc());/cast<LoadInst>(LV)->setDebugLoc(LI->getDebugLoc());\n      LV = new ICmpInst(ICI, ICmpInst::ICMP_NE, LV,                   │
│ ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext()), 0), "initpred");/' llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp && sed -i 's/LV = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext()),       │
│ 0);/LV = ConstantInt::getFalse(GV->getContext());/' llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp && sed -i 's/LV = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt8Ty(GV->getContext()), 1);/LV =                 │
│ ConstantInt::getTrue(GV->getContext());/' llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp                                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
