│ THOUGHT: The crash remains because we only bailed out after creating and using the synthesized init flag. To avoid introducing @g.init entirely in atomic scenarios, we must bail out    │
│ before any transformation, including before creating InitBool and NewGV. I will insert an early atomic-uses check right before the InitBool creation and return nullptr if any           │
│ load/store to GV is atomic, thus skipping the whole optimization safely.                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/GlobalVariable \*InitBool = new GlobalVariable/ i \  // Bail out early if any use of the global is atomic.\n  for (User *U : GV->users()) {\n    if (auto *LI =                 │
│ dyn_cast<LoadInst>(U)) { if (LI->isAtomic()) return nullptr; }\n    if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(U)) { if (SI->isAtomic()) return nullptr; }\n  }\n'                               │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/GlobalOpt.cpp                                                                                                                                                    │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
